  "body": "***Type***: Bug\n\n***Summary***: If to clear \"Search\" input on Chats view we hide search input (along with 'Cancel' button). Along with that, we give no ability to cancel chat searching and only white screen keep staying on 'Chats' view. So there are no chats that were present on the 'Chats' view are shown and available for open. \nAfter app re-launch everything is fine and chats are displayed as expected\n\n#### Expected behavior\n`Search input` and `Cancel` are shown on 'Chats' view after clear Search input with the entered keyword in Search input\n\n#### Actual behavior\nNo `Search input`, no `Cancel`, no list of chats are shown on 'Chats' view after clear Search input with the entered keyword in Search input\n\n![32132131231211111111](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/62044115-cd94aa00-b20a-11e9-9b8b-39ecf765499f.gif)\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status and create new account\n- Join any public chat\n- Navigate back to main 'Chats' view\n- Pull-down the screen so 'Search' input appears\n- Enter any keyword in Search input\n- Clear the 'Search' input\n\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: Delelop/Release 0.14.0\n- Operating System: Android and iOS",
